# Agent 1 — Ingestion

## Contract

Read `agents/01_ingestion.md` before editing this area. Authoritative outputs and CLI shape are defined there.

## Hard rules

- Use **`urllib`** from stdlib. Do **NOT** add `requests`, `wikipedia-api`, `mwclient`, or other Wikipedia wrappers — native-first per the PRD.
- Endpoints to use:
  - `https://en.wikipedia.org/api/rest_v1/page/summary/<title>` — summary + canonical URL
  - `https://en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=query&prop=extracts&explaintext=1&titles=<title>&format=json` — full plain-text body
- Set `User-Agent: localchat-rag/1.0 (educational)`.
- Throttle: 100–200 ms sleep between requests. Backoff on HTTP errors.
- **Disambiguation guard:** if the API returns a disambiguation page, raise loudly. Never silently pick one of the candidates.
- **Idempotent:** re-running with the same roster is a no-op unless `--force`. Track via SHA-256 of `text` in `_manifest.json`.
- **Plain text only:** strip wiki markup, refs, and infobox markers from extracts.

## Output schema (one file per entity)

`data/raw/<type>/<slug>.json`:
```json
{
  "entity_name": "Albert Einstein",
  "type": "person",
  "wikipedia_url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Albert_Einstein",
  "fetched_at": "2026-04-27T20:30:00Z",
  "title": "Albert Einstein",
  "summary": "...",
  "text": "...full plain-text body..."
}
```

`data/raw/_manifest.json` lists ingested entities with hash + fetch timestamp.

## Out of scope here

- Chunking → Agent 2 (`chunking/`)
- Embedding → Agent 2 (`embedding/`)
- Languages other than English (MVP scope)

If a change here implies an `_manifest.json` schema change or a roster format change, update `product_prd.md` first.
